<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
The holotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pierretia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pierretia catharosa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pierretia catharosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deposited in CDCP and not currently available for loan and study. 
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B36" refString="Verves, YuG, 2020. An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera). Suplementos del Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 1: 1 - 68" title="An annotated list of Chinese Sarcophagidae (Diptera)." volume="1" year="2020">Verves (2020</bibRefCitation>
: 36) listed 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. catharosa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="catharosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">P. catharosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. genuforceps" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="genuforceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">S. genuforceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although not as a new synonym. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Li, ZZ" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="526 - 539" refId="B42" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2007. Sarcophagidae. In: Li, ZZ, Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 526 - 539" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Leigongshan Landscape." year="2007">Wei and Yang (2007)</bibRefCitation>
gave a detailed description and a somewhat schematical illustration of the phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sarcophaga (Bellieriomima) genuforceps Thomas, 1949; phallus, lateral view A adapted from Lehrer (2012) B adapted from Wei and Yang (2007, as Pierretia catharosa)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706067" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">2B</figureCitation>
), which is here considered sufficient justification for the synonymy. 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="43 - 58" refId="B45" refString="Xue, Wq, Verves, YuG, 2009. Perisimyia perisi, a new genus and species from South China (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 33 (1-2): 43 - 58" title="Perisimyia perisi, a new genus and species from South China (Diptera: Sarcophagidae)." volume="33" year="2009">Xue and Verves (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 53) considered 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. genuforceps" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="genuforceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">S. genuforceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fan &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" genus="Pachystyleta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachystyleta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pachystyleta</taxonomicName>
Fan &amp; Chen, 1992, as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Myorhina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Myorhina" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Myorhina</taxonomicName>
Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830, whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehrer, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Fragmenta Dipterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="14 - 18" refId="B15" refString="Lehrer, AZ, 2010. Le genre Pachystyleta Fan et Chen de la faune de Chine et sa composition specifique (Diptera, Sarcophagidae). Fragmenta Dipterologica 26: 14 - 18" title="Le genre Pachystyleta Fan et Chen de la faune de Chine et sa composition specifique (Diptera, Sarcophagidae)." volume="26" year="2010">Lehrer (2010</bibRefCitation>
: 18) raised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fan &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" genus="Pachystyleta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachystyleta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pachystyleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to genus rank. We prefer to follow the classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T" journalOrPublisher="International" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 558" refId="B22" refString="Pape, T, 1996. Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology. International 8: 1 - 558" title="Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology." volume="8" year="1996">Pape (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fan &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" genus="Pachystyleta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachystyleta" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pachystyleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Bellieriomima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bellieriomima" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Bellieriomima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the latter as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">sensu lato</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.83267.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706067" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga (Bellieriomima) genuforceps" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genuforceps" subGenus="Bellieriomima">Sarcophaga (Bellieriomima) genuforceps</taxonomicName>
Thomas, 1949; phallus, lateral view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">A</emphasis>
adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehrer, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica, Bari" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="3 - 158" refId="B16" refString="Lehrer, AZ, 2012. Taxonomic Atlas of the postabdominal structures Sarcophagidae (Insecta, Diptera) Vol. II. Entomologica, Bari 44: 3 - 158" title="Taxonomic Atlas of the postabdominal structures Sarcophagidae (Insecta, Diptera) Vol. II." volume="44" year="2012">Lehrer (2012)</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">B</emphasis>
adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Wei, LM" editor="Li, ZZ" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="526 - 539" refId="B42" refString="Wei, LM, Yang, ZH, 2007. Sarcophagidae. In: Li, ZZ, Yang, MF, Jin, DC, Eds., Insects from Leigongshan Landscape. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang: 526 - 539" title="Sarcophagidae." volumeTitle="Insects from Leigongshan Landscape." year="2007">Wei and Yang (2007</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wei &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Pierretia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pierretia catharosa" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Pierretia catharosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
